<number box="[688,716,1060,1085]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" value="15.0">15</number>
described species with only 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1332,1060,1085]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Trichopygomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triramula">
<emphasis box="[1036,1332,1060,1085]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Trichopygomyia triramula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded previously in 
<collectingCountry box="[306,391,1095,1120]" name="Mexico" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Mexico</collectingCountry>
based on specimens collected in Veracruz (Ibáñez-Bernal 
<emphasis box="[1051,1100,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1115,1175,1096,1120]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" value="2011.0">2011</number>
). This species was also collected during the present study.
